rComments: She's actually one of the sweetest, nicest professors. She's organized, clear, and really aware about what we as student want to explore. Her reading list is both unique and interesting (lots of books from queer peoples and POC, as well as contemporary classics like Maus). She really cares that you enjoy the class.
Miriam is a great teacher! She cares about her students, she's an organized lecturer, and she brings real political issues into the classroom. Thoughtful and fair.
